		<title>13COMBE FLOREY (CONT)</title>
		<content>                                       
                                       
 Certainly, he suffered such a sentence
 for, as it was said, disembowelling   
 the body  of his late wife and he was 
 only absolved in 1314 when he returned
 her heart; but his wife was called    
 Mary, not Maud, which makes the story 
 of the nun not quite accurate, though 
 it leaves the Meriets with a penchant 
 for heart burials. In the church you  
 can see a poor box dated 1634 and on  
 it are written the words "Remember the
 poor" put there after a bishop's visit
 by conscientious churchwardens.       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
